OL,3,CThe Miners' Strike: Communities
OL,4,Creflect on year that 'changed Wales
OL,5,Cforever'
OL,7,F"Things like the stockpiling of coal
OL,8,Fwas all planned by the government and
OL,9,Fit was planned well. They were well
OL,10,Fahead of the game.
OL,12,F"But In my heart I'll always be a
OL,13,Fminer, and I'm proud of it too."
OL,15,FWayne Thomas worked in Abernant
OL,16,FColliery, and his wife Debra gave
OL,17,Fbirth to their daughter Danielle
OL,18,Fduring the strike.
