OL,3,CThe Miners' Strike: Communities
OL,4,Creflect on year that 'changed Wales
OL,5,Cforever'
OL,7,F"The food parcels were a lifeline, we
OL,8,Fhave never forgotten what that meant.
OL,9,FThe solidarity shown within mining
OL,10,Fcommunities is something that leaves a
OL,11,Flegacy."
OL,13,FKay Bowen was the coordinator for the
OL,14,FNeath District Miners Support group,
OL,15,Fwhich included the communities of
OL,16,FBanwen, Onllwyn and Ystradgynlais.
OL,18,F"I found inside me something that I
OL,19,Fdidn't know was there.
