OL,3,CThe Miners' Strike: Communities
OL,4,Creflect on year that 'changed Wales
OL,5,Cforever'
OL,7,F"It totally took over my life. I was
OL,8,Fextremely shy before the strike, I had
OL,9,Fno confidence, but the confidence I
OL,10,Fgained from doing that altered my life
OL,11,Ftremendously.
OL,13,F"Without the little army of people who
OL,14,Fhelped, the miners would have had to
OL,15,Fgive up on the strike.
OL,17,F"They wouldn't have had enough food to
OL,18,Fgo on."
