OL,3,CThe Miners' Strike: Communities
OL,4,Creflect on year that 'changed Wales
OL,5,Cforever'
OL,7,FChristine Powell was treasurer of the
OL,8,FGroup, which supported 1,000 families
OL,9,Fa week during the strike.
OL,11,F"We had support from trade unions in
OL,12,FFrance, Sweden, Germany and across
OL,13,FEurope.
OL,15,F"At Christmas, we managed to get
OL,16,Fpresents for all the children and
OL,17,Fevery striking family had a turkey.
OL,19,F"It wasn't about pay, it wasn't about
OL,20,Fconditions, it was about livelihoods.
