OL,3,CThe Miners' Strike: Communities
OL,4,Creflect on year that 'changed Wales
OL,5,Cforever'
OL,7,F"The pit was the mother of the
OL,8,Fvillage, and when that went it was a
OL,9,Fdomino effect."
OL,11,FJohn Wilshire was a miner at Point of
OL,12,FAyr colliery in Flintshire, the only
OL,13,Fpit in Wales to remain open throughout
OL,14,Fthe strike.
OL,16,F"I voted to go on strike, but the
OL,17,Fmajority at the pit didn't.
OL,19,F"I'm a democrat, so it was like being
OL,20,Ftrapped between the devil and the deep
OL,21,Fblue sea.
