OL,3,CThe Miners' Strike: Communities
OL,4,Creflect on year that 'changed Wales
OL,5,Cforever'
OL,7,FJayne believes the strike was a
OL,8,Fcritical moment for the lives of women
OL,9,Facross Wales.
OL,11,F"Women were rising up, coming out of
OL,12,Ftheir houses, and they weren't going
OL,13,Fback.
OL,15,F"It was the year of my O-Levels. I was
OL,16,Fshy, I was bullied because of a
OL,17,Fbirthmark on my face.
OL,19,F"Everything changed for me when the
OL,20,FLGSM (Lesbians and Gays Support the
OL,21,FMiners) came up from London.
