OL,3,CThe Miners' Strike: Communities
OL,4,Creflect on year that 'changed Wales
OL,5,Cforever'
OL,7,F"It made me realise people believe in
OL,8,Fyou if you believe in a cause.
OL,10,F"The legacy for me is that realisation
OL,11,Fthat you can do what you need to do."
OL,13,FWynne Phillips was a police sergeant
OL,14,Fduring the strike, working across the
OL,15,FSouth Wales Valleys.
OL,17,FHe found himself policing people from
OL,18,Fwithin the very community he called
OL,19,Fhome.
