OL,3,CThe Miners' Strike: Communities
OL,4,Creflect on year that 'changed Wales
OL,5,Cforever'
OL,7,F"It was a difficult time, I had
OL,8,Fsympathy for the mining community,
OL,9,Ftheir jobs were going they had to
OL,10,Fstand up and fight for that.
OL,12,F"We were policing good people, who we
OL,13,Fhad respect for, who were friends of
OL,14,Fours.
OL,16,F"We were seen as the force preventing
OL,17,Fthem keeping their jobs, but I had a
OL,18,Funiform on and I had a job to do."
