OL,3,CThe Miners' Strike: Communities
OL,4,Creflect on year that 'changed Wales
OL,5,Cforever'
OL,7,FRoger Tiley, a photographer embedded
OL,8,Fin the mining communities of the
OL,9,FRhondda Valley during the strike,
OL,10,Fbelieves the dispute changed the very
OL,11,Fway we define community.
OL,13,F"I never thought, 40 years on, that
OL,14,Fthat bustling pit at Maerdy, where I
OL,15,Floved coming to to take photos, would
OL,16,Fever disappear. But it did, and it
OL,17,Fdisappeared quickly."
OL,19,F"When a pit closed, that culture, that
OL,20,Fcamaraderie disappeared," he said.
OL,21,F"It's not the same place now.
